---
import OpenClawLayout from "../../layouts/OpenClawLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/cheatsheet-shared.css";
---

<OpenClawLayout
  title="OpenClaw Tips & Tricks — changelogs.info"
  description="Quick wins, hidden features, common mistakes, and workflow combos for OpenClaw."
  currentPage="tips"
>
  <div class="cs-wrapper">

    <section class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__emoji">💡</div>
      <h1 class="oc-headline cs-hero__title">
        Tips &<span class="cs-hero__accent"> Tricks</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="cs-hero__sub">Quick wins, hidden features, and the mistakes everyone makes once.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="cs-grid">

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">Quick Wins</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Run openclaw doctor first</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Catches 80% of problems before you waste time debugging. Always start here.</p>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> openclaw doctor</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Dashboard works without messaging apps</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Use <code>openclaw dashboard</code> to validate the full stack before adding Telegram or Discord.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Memory is plain .md files</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Memory lives in your workspace as markdown files. Read and edit them directly — search with the memory_search tool.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Check which skills actually work</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> openclaw skills check</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Shows which skills are runnable vs just installed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Tail the gateway log</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> tail -f ~/.openclaw/logs/gateway.log</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Beats guessing when debugging channel issues.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">Hidden Features</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Share skills across agents</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Agents can share skills by symlinking skill directories — no duplication needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">HEARTBEAT.md drives health checks</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">HEARTBEAT.md drives automated health check crons — keep it updated and run it on a schedule.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Multiple agents, different models</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">You can run multiple agents pointing at different models on the same gateway.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--warning">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">Common Mistakes</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Setting up Discord before proving the gateway works</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Always use <code>openclaw dashboard</code> first. Prove the stack works before adding channel complexity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Putting secrets in workspace files</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Use <code>~/.openclaw/secrets/</code> only. Workspace files are visible to agents.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Using rm on workspace files</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Use trash instead so you can recover files. <code>rm</code> is permanent.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Skipping openclaw doctor</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">When something breaks, doctor should be your first move, not your last resort.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="oc-headline cs-panel__title">Workflow Combos</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Mobile-first setup (15 min)</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Telegram → openclaw dashboard → phone pairing → done. The fastest path to a working mobile AI assistant.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Fleet pattern</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">One gateway, 5 agents, each with a different persona and model. Use symlinked skills to share capabilities without duplication.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</OpenClawLayout>
